Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.80,0:00:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.59,0:00:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We just need to cover this up properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.01,0:00:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I could use a drink about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.14,0:00:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I got whiskey bonbons.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.02,0:00:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.90,0:00:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This was a present from that hottie.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.40,0:00:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? You look depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.12,0:00:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't trust anyone anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.41,0:00:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You can tell me if you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.75,0:00:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I believed in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.21,0:00:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Of all people, I was sure\Nthat Inspector Zeman wouldn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.71,0:00:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.18,0:00:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I believed in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.85,0:01:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now,\Nthe only person that I can trust…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.61,0:01:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.25,0:02:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,An unbelievably horrific crime has\Noccurred at the Prague Police Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.21,0:02:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Commissioner Hamrlík,\NChief Detective Patera
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.88,0:02:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and Detective Janáček were\Ndiscovered poisoned to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.97,0:03:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would the murderer commit\Nsuch a brazen act?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.06,0:03:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There have been rumors that\Nsome within the Prague Police
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.10,0:03:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,have connections with\Nformer Czechoslovakia secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.90,0:03:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's possible that these murders\Ncould expose an even greater scandal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.19,0:03:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Someone came out of the station!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.07,0:03:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you figured out who the murderer is?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.57,0:03:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it true that the poison\Nthat was used is a muscle relaxant?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.41,0:03:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Commissioner Hamrlík\Nhave connections with the secret police?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.17,0:03:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.13,0:03:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this connected with the murder\Nof Inspector Zeman a week ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.59,0:03:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,These things\Nare still under investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.93,0:03:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That must mean you believe\Nall these incidents are related, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.02,0:03:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No. As I have said, though that's\Na possibility, we're still--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.77,0:03:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but this detective\Nis in charge of a different case.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.36,0:03:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn to button your lip.\NNow, get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.86,0:03:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.95,0:04:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,When will you hold\Na proper press conference?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.70,0:04:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll hold a press conference\Nwhen we have something to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.79,0:04:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Be patient until then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.08,0:04:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it taking you so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.56,0:04:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had it up to here with you people!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.64,0:04:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you need to question them again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.02,0:04:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.02,0:04:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been ordered to investigate\Nthe whole case over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.44,0:04:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I've finished speaking with the children\Nwho were taken to other orphanages.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.62,0:04:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Put yourself in these children's shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.79,0:04:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They witnessed the deaths of Mr. Petrov,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.62,0:04:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the man who'd been like a father to them,\Nas well as his maid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.75,0:04:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them still have nightmares.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.67,0:05:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like them to forget all about it\Nas soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.35,0:05:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But I doubt they'll forget that\Nfor the rest of their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.02,0:05:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the people they loved\Nso dearly were murdered!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.07,0:05:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you 15 minutes each.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.40,0:05:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And no questions that are too graphic.\NUnderstand?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.03,0:05:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Living there was a lot of fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.74,0:05:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Petrov and Anna were nice people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.16,0:05:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.67,0:05:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask you about\Nthe day of their deaths?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.34,0:05:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer came that day,\Nbut had he been there before?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.47,0:05:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No. That was the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.47,0:05:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know why he was there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.39,0:05:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.26,0:05:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Were Mr. Petrov\Nand Mr. Grimmer getting along well?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.27,0:05:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it didn't look like\Nthey got along all that well, but…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.65,0:05:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But what?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.94,0:05:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They were talking about complicated stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.65,0:06:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You boys speak a little German, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.07,0:06:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What were they saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.66,0:06:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "This place is unlicensed."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.20,0:06:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And, "I'll report you to the police."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.16,0:06:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,-That's what Mr. Grimmer said?\N-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.17,0:06:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And they said words like "education"\Nand "experiment."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.67,0:06:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,"Experiment"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.96,0:06:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.88,0:06:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.63,0:06:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay if you don't want to\Nremember those things, Honza.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.64,0:06:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They also said "Kinderheim 511."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.64,0:06:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,"Kinderheim 511"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.14,0:06:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.69,0:06:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.73,0:06:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.65,0:06:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no place by that name\Nin the Czech Republic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.41,0:06:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you tell me what Mr. Grimmer was like?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.66,0:06:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a really nice guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.25,0:06:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So you think so too, Izzy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.58,0:06:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We played soccer together!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.67,0:06:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't very good at it though.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.09,0:07:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But Mr. Grimmer looked like\Nhe was having a lot of fun too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.92,0:07:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He fell on his butt\Nwhen he tried to head the ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.89,0:07:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He's probably worse than Honza.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.01,0:07:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Also…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.93,0:07:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard you were like a leader\Nat that orphanage, Antonin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.44,0:07:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like I was a leader or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.48,0:07:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I just happened to be\Na little older than the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.69,0:07:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you tell me about that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.95,0:07:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean about Mr. Grimmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.03,0:07:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Honza and Izzy told me\Nyou asked about Mr. Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.83,0:07:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. So, what can you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.62,0:07:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a nice guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.34,0:07:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think Mr. Grimmer killed them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.38,0:07:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No. That's not why I'm asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.22,0:07:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer isn't the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.89,0:07:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He was playing soccer with us,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.22,0:07:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and Mr. Petrov and Anna were\Nalready dead when we got back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.39,0:07:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I already told all this\Nto the cops before.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.14,0:08:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw a beautiful blonde woman\Nwhen she left our place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.82,0:08:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to arrest him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.16,0:08:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Arrest who?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.16,0:08:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.87,0:08:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we don't know who did it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.30,0:08:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to be seeing him soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.88,0:08:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We arranged to meet.\NWe even chose the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.68,0:08:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.47,0:08:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.93,0:08:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?\NWe might arrest him, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.69,0:08:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.\NThere's no way he would ever kill anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.91,0:08:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hi.\N-Hi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.87,0:09:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while.\NYou have been doing all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.00,0:09:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been doing great!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.50,0:09:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure you didn't cry a lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.67,0:09:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy wet his bed twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.26,0:09:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay. Even I wet my bed\Nuntil I was a lot older than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.51,0:09:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.44,0:09:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Antonin, do you have what I gave you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.49,0:09:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.53,0:09:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You took good care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.49,0:09:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This is something very important\NMr. Petrov left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.66,0:09:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. I haven't got much time,\Nso I'll be going.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.50,0:09:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care, you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.21,0:09:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's play soccer, Mr. Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.88,0:09:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but I really don't have time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.42,0:09:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me introduce you to our new friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.51,0:09:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, all right.\NJust for a little bit though.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.35,0:10:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,-All right!\N-All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.86,0:10:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,-Pass!\N-It's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.94,0:10:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Pass it quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.28,0:10:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Go! Now's our chance! Pass it here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.95,0:10:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.91,0:10:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll be easy to steal!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.17,0:10:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to defend better than that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.38,0:10:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.84,0:10:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,-Come on!\N-Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.97,0:10:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Here goes! There!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.44,0:10:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.49,0:10:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you here to arrest me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.53,0:10:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go pulling a gun. The kids will see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.79,0:11:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Then put your gun down where I can see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.46,0:11:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I ain't got no gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.08,0:11:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You tossed it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.17,0:11:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never carried a gun in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.60,0:11:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it you who killed Inspector Zeman?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.56,0:11:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.89,0:11:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I was half dead\Nfrom being tortured.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.86,0:11:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Your nails…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.44,0:11:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't me who shot the gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.36,0:11:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But I may have killed the other two.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.95,0:11:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I just don't remember though.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.87,0:11:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.62,0:11:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Who said you could rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.92,0:11:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The other team is short a player now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.63,0:11:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry about that, but I'm exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.97,0:11:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It was me who told the kids\Nto invite you to play soccer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.93,0:12:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been watching the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.64,0:12:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do you think? Am I the murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.02,0:12:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.77,0:12:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,These last few days,\NI've been betrayed by so many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.11,0:12:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no idea who to believe in anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.78,0:12:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only truly believe in yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.66,0:12:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Ultimately, the only person\Nyou can trust is yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.87,0:12:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to arrest me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.25,0:12:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you promise not to leave town?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.88,0:12:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you staying now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.18,0:12:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pavla Hotel, room 302.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.35,0:12:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you become convinced I'm the murderer,\Ncome get me anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.86,0:12:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.15,0:12:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's the cause of these murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.49,0:13:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the key to a safe deposit box.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.54,0:13:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This sign?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.29,0:13:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This thing is ancient.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.09,0:13:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard it was the sign for a pub\N200 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.76,0:13:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's still here\Neven though the pub isn't anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.89,0:13:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pretty darn faded,\Nbut it's like a landmark on this street.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.14,0:13:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Through the war\Nand all kinds of disasters,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.44,0:13:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it somehow survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.27,0:13:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the fire a little over a decade ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.90,0:13:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.24,0:13:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, a woman and her child\Nmoved into the second floor here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.03,0:13:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,She was a beautiful woman,\Nbut awfully gloomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.20,0:13:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,She rarely went out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.29,0:13:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard she was even using a fake name.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.42,0:13:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then suddenly one day a black car\Ndrove up and took her and her kid away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.05,0:14:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There were rumors she was involved with\Nsome kind of anti-government movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.89,0:14:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That kind of government terrorism\Nhappened a lot back then
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.68,0:14:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,at the end of the communist era.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.02,0:14:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were terrible times.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.10,0:14:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,People suddenly disappearing like that\Nwasn't a rare occurrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.49,0:14:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The woman who was taken away,\Ndid she have twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.20,0:14:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No. She only had one child.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.99,0:14:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The child had a very pretty face.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.91,0:14:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it a boy or a girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.91,0:14:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait… Come to think of it,\NI don't remember which they were.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.67,0:14:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You know how it can be hard to tell\Nwhat they are when they're so little.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.51,0:14:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone was appalled\Nat how they not only took the woman away,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.47,0:14:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but her innocent child as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.64,0:14:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the fire happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.35,0:14:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought nobody was there\Nwhere the fire started,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.35,0:14:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but the child was found in the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.44,0:15:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They must have released just the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.78,0:15:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The kid must have been dying of hunger\Nand started a fire to cook something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.91,0:15:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.20,0:15:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure after they were rescued\Nfrom the fire, they went missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.25,0:15:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows where they went.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.54,0:15:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What if they were twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.00,0:15:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.50,0:15:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,One twin was taken away,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.38,0:15:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but the other one\Ncould have been left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.01,0:15:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see. I guess that's a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.31,0:15:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But why are you so sure\Nthat there were twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.77,0:15:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,THREE FROGS
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.40,0:15:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked into that tall guy, Grimmer,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.20,0:15:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that you said\NI should probably investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.99,0:15:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think he's the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.41,0:15:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.74,0:15:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Mr. Suk. I'm just a novice\Nand don't know what I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.96,0:15:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not a bad guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.96,0:16:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I was investigating that guy\Nand I found out a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.34,0:16:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, I was frantic because I wanted\Nto avenge Inspector Zeman's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.01,0:16:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But as I was investigating,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.81,0:16:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I found out that Inspector Zeman,\Nwho I respected as a detective,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.64,0:16:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,was actually a dirty cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.69,0:16:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the commissioner and two\Nof my seniors were poisoned to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.65,0:16:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When I heard about their poisoning,\NI was dumbfounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.66,0:16:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I wondered just how far\Nthe darkness had crept into this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.33,0:16:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Darkness?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.79,0:16:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the Czechoslovakia secret police\Nare thought to be behind all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.46,0:16:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,As part of the former\NMinistry of Internal Affairs,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.96,0:16:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they were pawns of the Soviet Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.09,0:16:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,About a decade ago during the\Ndemocratic revolution, it was disbanded.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.60,0:16:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The leaders were put on trial,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.72,0:16:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but many members escaped\Nand went underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.06,0:17:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, they're plotting\Nto regain their former power.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.10,0:17:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.23,0:17:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But why do\Nso many people have to die for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.82,0:17:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it really only the former secret police\Nthat is behind these murders?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.45,0:17:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Just how much of the darkness\Nfrom their world
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.45,0:17:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,has encroached on this world we live in?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.87,0:17:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't trust anyone anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.42,0:17:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But Mr. Grimmer told me something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.00,0:17:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "Ultimately, the only person\Nyou can trust is yourself."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.92,0:17:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When he told me that,\Nhe gave me something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.43,0:17:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.39,0:17:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This must be boring you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.76,0:17:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.06,0:17:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I still don't even know your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.98,0:17:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's all right.\NYou don't have to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.86,0:17:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Until now,\NI've always believed you build trust
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.20,0:17:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,when you learn a person's name\Nand about their past.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.03,0:17:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can talk to you about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.17,0:18:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Both my parents are teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.88,0:18:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When my dad got involved
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.26,0:18:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in the democracy movement,\Nthe police kept tabs on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.76,0:18:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So my mom divorced him.\NShe said it was for my sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.14,0:18:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When I said I wanted to be\Na police detective,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.65,0:18:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,my mom was completely against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.27,0:18:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you want to become a detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.44,0:18:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,My friends at the bar\Ntold you before, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.11,0:18:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean it was because\Nof detective shows?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.03,0:18:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Since I was a kid,\Nit was always my dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.99,0:18:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I was always playing detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.29,0:18:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Bang!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.75,0:18:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.67,0:18:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.06,0:19:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what did he give you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.86,0:19:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier, you said\Nthat Mr. Grimmer gave you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.57,0:19:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right. It's a safe deposit box key.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.12,0:19:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A safe deposit box?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.74,0:19:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There's some pretty important stuff in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.04,0:19:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know about that German man
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.87,0:19:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,who ran the illegal orphanage, Petrov,\Nwho was murdered?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.33,0:19:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.75,0:19:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, there are records from
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.84,0:19:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the human experiments\Nthat Petrov ran in the safe deposit box.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.51,0:19:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that those are the cause\Nof these recent murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.14,0:19:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.14,0:19:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you dare tell the police\Nor anyone about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.10,0:19:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't solve this on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.23,0:19:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-Your mother…\N-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.36,0:19:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely you know why your mother\Nwas against you joining the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.91,0:20:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She was worried\Nthat something awful might happen to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.12,0:20:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a bad feeling about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.25,0:20:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So don't you tell anyone about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.08,0:20:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I feel the same way\Nthat your mother feels.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.47,0:20:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.77,0:20:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.40,0:20:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.65,0:20:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.48,0:20:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna Liebert.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.19,0:20:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna… Such a nice name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.20,0:20:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you're German.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.70,0:20:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,-See you later.\N-Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.20,0:20:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.20,0:21:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening, Mr. Trnka.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.70,0:21:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Nice night, isn't it, Anna?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.08,0:21:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good evening, Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.25,0:21:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening, Ms. Jalka.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.26,0:22:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A safe deposit box key, eh?
